definition.value: A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid that is pyridine in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a carboxy group.
A cyclohexadienecarboxylic acid having the C=C bonds at the 1- and 3-positions, the carboxylic acid at the 1-position and two hydroxy substituents at the 5- and 6-positions.
An aminobenzenesulfonate that is the conjugate base of 2-aminobenzenesulfonic acid.
A homopolymer macromolecule consisting of repeating glycerol-1-phosphate units.
